{"default_components":[{"id":"c6_wifi"}],"description":"Waveshare ESP32-P4-WIFI6-POE-ETH with the ESP32-P4NRW32 (dual-core RISC-V @ 400MHz, 32MB flash, 32MB PSRAM) and an ESP32-C6-MINI-1U co-processor with external antenna connector. The ESP32-P4 has no built-in radio; Wi-Fi 6 works out of the box through the onboard ESP32-C6 co-processor. 100M RJ45 Ethernet (IP101 PHY) with PoE, MIPI DSI display and MIPI CSI camera connectors, microSD slot, microphone + speaker header, USB-A OTG and USB-C ports.","docs_url":"https://www.waveshare.com/wiki/ESP32-P4-WIFI6-POE-ETH","esphome":{"board":"esp32-p4-evboard","engineering_sample":true,"framework":"esp-idf","logger_hardware_uart":"UART0","platform":"esp32","variant":"esp32p4"},"featured_components":[{"component_id":"esp32_hosted","description":"Onboard ESP32-C6 running ESP-Hosted over SDIO gives the radio-less ESP32-P4 Wi-Fi 6. Installed automatically in every new device — the wifi block only works while this is present. If the C6 never comes up on your unit, try active_high false.","fields":{"active_high":{"value":true},"clk_pin":{"locked":true,"value":"GPIO18"},"cmd_pin":{"locked":true,"value":"GPIO19"},"d0_pin":{"locked":true,"value":"GPIO14"},"d1_pin":{"locked":true,"value":"GPIO15"},"d2_pin":{"locked":true,"value":"GPIO16"},"d3_pin":{"locked":true,"value":"GPIO17"},"reset_pin":{"locked":true,"value":"GPIO54"},"type":{"locked":true,"value":"sdio"},"variant":{"locked":true,"value":"ESP32C6"}},"id":"c6_wifi","locked_pins":{"clk_pin":18,"cmd_pin":19,"d0_pin":14,"d1_pin":15,"d2_pin":16,"d3_pin":17,"reset_pin":54},"multi_conf":false,"name":"Wi-Fi via ESP32-C6 co-processor"},{"component_id":"ethernet","description":"Built-in IP101 Ethernet PHY (RMII) — selected automatically when a device is created without Wi-Fi credentials.","fields":{"clk":{"locked":true,"value":{"mode":"CLK_EXT_IN","pin":"GPIO50"}},"mdc_pin":{"locked":true,"value":"GPIO31"},"mdio_pin":{"locked":true,"value":"GPIO52"},"phy_addr":{"locked":true,"value":1},"po